						<summary>

						<p>Slab (broken) set up below the slope in front of the Narasimha temple on the hill.</p>						

						<p>This undated record may be assigned to the 16th century on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>Damaged and fragmentary. It seems to refer to the consecration of some deity and construction of a temple to the same, probably by a certain chief (name lost) holding the <hi rend="italic">nāyaṅkara</hi> of the village Peṇḍlimaṟṟi. It also appears to register a grant of land obviously to the same deity and also to a certain Anaṁtōju who seems to have constructed the temple.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
